\begin{align*}
x &= \frac{5 \pm \sqrt{25 + 4 \cdot 1 \cdot 36}}{2}\\
&= \frac{5 \pm \sqrt{169}}{2}\\
&= \frac{5 \pm 13}{2}
\end{align*}This gives us 2 possible values for $x$, namely
\begin{align*}
